  m_Name: Dining Room Relic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Imported Wine
  description: 'Wine was considered a luxury product in the Netherlands during the
    18th and 19th centuries, especially in northern regions such as Groningen where
    grapes could not easily be grown. Wealthy households imported wines from countries
    like France, Germany, and Spain to serve during formal dinners and social gatherings,
    making wine a symbol of status and refinement. '
